\Pr(x \in E \text{ and } x \in R) = \Pr(x \in E)\Pr(x \in R)
\Pr(x \in R) > 0
\begin{align} \Pr(x \in E \mid x \in R) &= \frac{Pr(x \in E \text{ and } x \in R)}{\Pr(x \in R)}\\ &= \frac{\Pr(x \in E)\Pr(x \in R)}{\Pr(x \in R)}\\ &= \Pr(x \in E) \end{align}
